// So in the scripts section, its usually good practice to add a start command to start the server. 
// So I added the start command in package.json, now all you have to do is go to the working directory and type in
// "npm start" and the server/script will start .

Also it gets annoying as hell when your editing your node.js app, and you have to kill and restart the server everytime
whenever you make a change, so install nodemon to solve this problem. Then add in your package.json scripts
section, "nodemon index.js", and in the console, type in npm run dev